    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-08T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-08T06:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660F.116/163: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-08T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 8, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 8—9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. My No. 11, March 4, 11 a.m. Collection of laws and decrees of April 1st
                    contains regulation of National Bank concerning certain changes in the
                    Czechoslovak-German Clearing Arrangement provide for reichsmark payments on
                    transit goods through Germany at the following rates: cotton 2½%; other
                    merchandise 1 to 4%. Please see Commercial Attaché’s special reports numbers
                    140, 142 and 147.<note n="41" xml:id="d138fn41">Not found in Department
                        flies.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
